&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;A thought occurred to me (yes, it happens :P)... are the victims really even afk though?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;As if the trainers check to see how long someone has been sitting there before training....&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If these people are kiting these spots regularly as part of routine hunting, then either the people being trained have to have been there first, or had to have arrived after the kiting started? If the former, then why does the kiter have the right to kite over them? If the latter, then they are not AFK are they? Unless you are going to try to argue that they got there while afk too, and that they always manage to travel about in EQ while afk...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;It is easy to say someone you just&amp;nbsp;trained 'must have been afk' ... how do they disprove it after the fact?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Oh, and as for 'playing the game'... RL happens. Are you going to try to tell me that you log out every time you have to use the washroom? Or heat up some leftovers to eat while playing? Or answer the door? There is some risk in going AFK, but that risk is not normally considered to be that someone will knowingly train you not merely to avoid death but because they think their right to kite is greater than your right to stand in an otherwise safe place while AFK.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The implication that the AFK people are 'soaking up xps.' is again, just an assumption. If it is a task or mission, then they could be in PoK and get the xps (or if an MM, they would have to loot a crystal from in mission and could not be afk to do that). If they are being PL'd conventionally, the source of the xps has to be close, and would also likely be hit by the train. It can be argued that being PL'd is also 'not playing the game' but that arguement only appiles to those being PL'd not those doing the PL'ing, and also would not apply in boxing situations.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So again, just rationalizations on the part of the trainer as to why the zone is 'theirs,' and why (in their opinion) they should be able to train anyone they wish who gets in their way.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Blue servers are NOT reds. Some people just have trouble accepting that :(&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Pouncequick&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
