&lt;P&gt;First off, they're not being "trained".&amp;nbsp; In general this discussion is about people going AFK in places commonly used for kiting, or PvE in general.&amp;nbsp; If they happen to get agro for being stupidly AFK and die, they weren't trained.&amp;nbsp; If you go AFK at a zone in, by now you should know that accidental trains can occur, and if you're trained the ONLY complaint you might have for going AFK at a zone in spot, is IF the person leading the train didn't happen to /shout Train to zone, but of course, you were AFK anyway so you wouldn't of seen it, so does it really matter?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
If these people are kiting these spots regularly as part of routine hunting, then either the people being trained have to have been there first, or had to have arrived after the kiting started? If the former, then why does the kiter have the right to kite over them? If the latter, then they are not AFK are they? Unless you are going to try to argue that they got there while afk too, and that they always manage to travel about in EQ while afk...&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;If I'm kiting/quadding anywhere and you're stupid enough to stop right in my path, you are a dumb ass and deserve any amount of death this game can inflict upon you.&amp;nbsp; If you stop in the middle of a well known kiting area and do nothing for an extended period of time, 30 seconds to minutes to hours, if you're not doing anything not even pulling, then I --will-- pull mobs and kite that area.&amp;nbsp; If you're not AFK, it's no big deal unless something unexpected happens and I have to leave, if that happens, you're not AFK anyway so you can deal with the situation appropriately, so it's a wash.&amp;nbsp; However, if you expect anyone to pass up a prime kiting area because you happen to be in the middle of it doing nothing, you're sadly mistaken.&amp;nbsp; Trust me, your presence, or lack there of, in a kiting area makes ZERO difference to the decision making process of whether or not I will kite that area when you're obviously doing absolutely NOTHING with the area.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
It is easy to say someone you just&amp;nbsp;trained 'must have been afk' ... how do they disprove it after the fact?&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The fact that tells were sent with no response is a good indicator.&amp;nbsp; Another good indicator would be having had several kite's pass over them without issue, or their moving, or any tells from them, would be a good indicator.&amp;nbsp; Also, perhaps standing there getting beat on by mobs easily escapable by anyone with runspeed 5, or a sow potion, doing nothing to defend themselves or making ANY attempt at getting away would ALSO be another indicator.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Oh, and as for 'playing the game'... RL happens. Are you going to try to tell me that you log out every time you have to use the washroom? Or heat up some leftovers to eat while playing? Or answer the door? There is some risk in going AFK, but that risk is not normally considered to be that someone will knowingly train you not merely to avoid death but because they think their right to kite is greater than your right to stand in an otherwise safe place while AFK.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;One thing I DON'T do is stop in the middle of a PvE zone.&amp;nbsp; I'll park my butt in the closest obscure corner available that I can, make sure I'm invis, put up my AFK tag (cause it's a blue server).&amp;nbsp; If I can't find one, I have other options, INCLUDING options available to EVERYONE else, a GATE potion for example.&amp;nbsp; If I happen to be with a group, I'll put one of them on autofollow, let my group know I have to afk for a moment and take my chances.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;See it's not up to EVERYONE ELSE around you to garuntee your safety just because YOUR reallife happens to impose on EVERYONE ELSE'S play time.&amp;nbsp; You're not allowed to be that self-centered.&amp;nbsp; There is no "King of Earth" and even if there was such a position, I doubt the "King of Earth" would bother playing EQ.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
The implication that the AFK people are 'soaking up xps.' is again, just an assumption. If it is a task or mission, then they could be in PoK and get the xps (or if an MM, they would have to loot a crystal from in mission and could not be afk to do that). If they are being PL'd conventionally, the source of the xps has to be close, and would also likely be hit by the train. It can be argued that being PL'd is also 'not playing the game' but that arguement only appiles to those being PL'd not those doing the PL'ing, and also would not apply in boxing situations.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;So again, just rationalizations on the part of the trainer as to why the zone is 'theirs,' and why (in their opinion) they should be able to train anyone they wish who gets in their way.&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;By the same token the person boxing, or being PL'd or getting free exp and loot, or whatever, DOES NOT OWN THE ZONE EITHER.&amp;nbsp; Hell, they only have a tentative claim to the virtual cubic feet they're taking up in any zone, so to assume that everyone else has to be responsible for your safety because you're stupid enough to park your lazy ass near spot people commonly fight, kight, quad, spawn instances or whatever.&amp;nbsp; You're in a PvE zone, at any point in time someone else may accidentally agro something and create a train.&amp;nbsp; If you're not in control of your character enough to move out of the way, invis up, or whatever, you have no business complaining that you were trained.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Blue servers are NOT reds. Some people just have trouble accepting that :(&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Pouncequick&#xD;
